rComments: He's okay. Tests involve lots of memorization.
It was a very interesting course by a nice prof! Clear lectures, help at office hours, interesting stuff, and an easy pass if you study.
Really good professor! always kind, caring, and patient to the questions.
Interesting lectures, always helpful at his office, can explain things again if you need it. Cheerful and never tough on you! Very nice prof!

Articulate, patient, knowledgable. Tests gave plenty of time, and had well chosen questions that tested understanding (rather than straight memorization). Not a fan of the textbook, however (Contemporary Abstract Algebra).
He is an awesome professor. He is so patient with students' questions. He is knowledgable and explains concepts really well. Absolutely recommend him
